results.name: Number of prime power divisors of n that are <= sqrt(n).
link: Robert Israel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: nmax = 100; CoefficientList[Series[Sum[Boole[PrimePowerQ[k]] x^(k^2)/(1 - x^k), {k, 1, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x] // Rest
program: (PARI) a(n) = sumdiv(n, d, (d^2<=n) && isprimepower(d)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Apr 03 2020
